Mr. and Miss Winter, who had known her between 10 and 11 years; Mr. Smith and Mr. French about 4; Mr. Merryman 12 or 14;
Dorothy Kelly
almost 2; Mr. Seabrook 7; all gave her the character of an honest sober person. There were many others ready to appear to her character, but the Jury declared they were satisfied.
